th victims or risk assessment. Thus, different professionals from different fields must work together and concertedly, not only to be able to know why, and how, criminal conduct occurs, but also to be able to reduce its consequences and possible recidivism. For this reason, the aim of this international conference is to bring together specialists from the fields of Psychology, Law, Social Work, Forensic Science, Educators, and in general, people related to the Social Sciences and the Law. In turn, it is aimed at professionals, researchers and academics. ABSTRACTING & INDEXING Psychology and Law: Research for practice is covered by the following services: Directory of Open Access Books (DOAB) Google Scholar Naviga (Softweco) Primo Central (ExLibris) ReadCube Semantic Scholar Summon (ProQuest) TDOne (TDNet) WorldCat (OCLC)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aAlmeida, Iris S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArce, Ramón, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArce, Ramón, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aArias, Esther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBai, Shuliang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBo, Yang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCamplá, Xaviera, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDomínguez-Álvarez, Beatriz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFariña, Francisca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGancedo,